      <p parentName="article">{`HOLD UP! If all you do is change your `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`<form>`}</inlineCode>{` to `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`<Form>`}</inlineCode>{`, you made the UX a little worse. If you don't have the time or drive to do the rest of the job here, leave it as `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`<form>`}</inlineCode>{` so that the browser handles pending UI state (spinner in the favicon of the tab, progress bar in the address bar, etc.) If you simply use `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`<Form>`}</inlineCode>{` without implementing pending UI, the user will have no idea anything is happening when they submit a form.`}</p>
      <p parentName="article">{`Now let's add some pending UI so the user has a clue something happened when they submit. There's a hook called `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`usePendingFormSubmit`}</inlineCode>{`. When there is a pending form submit, Remix will give you the serialized version of the form as a `}<a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/FormData"><inlineCode parentName="p">{`FormData`}</inlineCode></a>{` object. You'll be most interested in the `}<a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/FormData/get"><inlineCode parentName="p">{`formData.get()`}</inlineCode></a>{` method..`}</p>
